Morning vibes in Iceland ☀️⁣ ⁣⁣
@djiglobal ⁣
🎶music by @comtruise ⁣
***Story time***⁣⁣
After a long day of exploring and driving to the west coast of Iceland we were stuck with the task of finding a campsite to view the northern lights. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
After much research we found that we were allowed to camp anywhere as long as we had the land owners permission. We noticed this farm on google maps and knew we had to give it a shot. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It was pitch black with only the northern lights to guide us but we still were able to find this farm and luckily the nice man that lived here was more then happy to let us stay the night. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We stayed up all night in awe by our first Aurora experience. As the sun began to rise we woke up, unzipped our tent and were completely blown away by where we had camped. Right on the cliffs overlooking Kirkjufell.⁣
⁣⁣
It was hands down the most memorable experience in Iceland! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If you made it this far thank you and I truly appreciate you!

Taking in views and facing fears || Getting up early for this sunrise was so rewarding especially since we ran into the coolest couple from Canada takings photos here. That’s Wendy dangling her feet from the ledge broken leg and all, her courage totally blew me away. Keep living Wendy!
Back in California enjoying last light and these beautiful coastal roads. Photo of me and #Moethevan by my good man @_kmil

Have you ever seen the sunset through a waterfall? This has to be one of the most unique waterfalls I’ve ever seen. You definitely get drenched but it’s totally worth it for this view from behind the falls. #onlyiniceland

I’ve seen so many images of this crashed US Navy plane in Iceland that I knew I wanted to put my own spin on it. Luckily I had my good friend @j_iskaros3 with me to help light up the inside of the plane. Who woulda thought a plane wreck can be so photogenic! #iceland
Moody morning at Kirkjufell Mountain|| 🎶 @si_bonobo #iceland

Crystal blue ice caves underneath Skaftafell glacier (The largest glacier in Europe). While hiking this glacier for the first time our guide Trim explained to us that these ice caves are formed in the summer time when the ice melt flows and creates river tubes underneath the glacier. It’s only towards the end of fall and start of winter when these ice caves begin to be accessible. This was only a tiny cave I can’t even imagine exploring some of the larger ones!

Hope you’re all ready for some Iceland spam! After 3 days Of chasing clear sky’s we thought we weren’t going to catch the Aurora but on the 4th night we found our clear sky’s and it was absolutely worth it! This place just can’t be real. #iceland
Shortly after taking this photos my good friend @j_iskaros3 and I Enjoyed this costal view while making the best egg and bacon burritos! All and all I’d say it was a great morning.
Thank you to the amazing Icelandic man who let us set up camp on his farm tonight. You the real MVP! #iceland

I think I’m gonna start shooing horses for a living. Who agrees! || Day one in Iceland and I’m already completely taken back at the beauty of this place.. and also the wind, a lot of wind! #icelandtravel

Late afternoon in Yosemite valley catching some unreal views of El Capitan|| Today I head to a one of my all time dream destination. Iceland! 🇮🇸 I’ve been dreaming of traveling to this photographers paradise for years now and I’m super stoked it’s finally happening. If you’ve ever been I’d love to hear about it!

Just spent the last 4 days totally disconnected from social media, instead I was connecting with some of the best humans. @descendonbend thank you for such a memorable experience! || ps: If you look closely you can see smoke billowing out of the TiPi.
Dreamy mornings in Thailand... #amazingthailand

Sri Lanka aka “the land of pleasant surprises”- Allan Massoud. One of my favorite parts of This beautiful country had to be the small mountain town of Ella. With numerous hikes and epic views it’s definitely a must see in Sri Lanka!
What’s your favorite part of the world? For me it would have to be Asia! There’s something so special about this region that has me coming back time and time again. #thailandtravel

Driving up to Bend, Oregon in one week with my Pops for @descendonbend one of the largest van meet ups in the country. Stoked to spend some quality time with the fam around the fire and enjoy those camp vibes!🚌 #moethevan
A 5 hr over night drive from SF to get here just in time for sunrise was brutal but having these falls all to ourselves was definitely worth it. Still can’t believe this is in California!

Sunsetting in the narrow streets of old Havana|| Havana had to be my all time favorite city’s to shoot. There was something new and fascinating around every corner! Who’s been or wants to visit Cuba? Let me know in the comments. #cubatravel
Chill camp nights where all you need is a roaring fire and a Dutch oven pizza 🍕😋 #moethevan

Hope everyone’s having a great weekend! This was one of my favourite places on my trip to Vietnam. A birds eye perspective of the floating villages off the coast of Cat Ba Island. Definitely missing this country! #whpperspective

One of my favorite things to do in Yosemite is post up at Taft point during sunset and watch Mother Nature do its thing...If Yosemite’s on your bucket list let me know in the comments! **Swipe to see how the light changes over a span of 15min**
Sunset views from the best seat in the house! #moethevan
5 miles down a washboard dirt road in the Mojave desert to get to these lava tubes. Absolutely worth the bumpy ride. Who would you explore these lava tubes with? Tag them in the comments ✌🏽
Finding peace in simplicity || Golden hour on the Oregon coast is something to behold. ✨

For this weeks @passionpassport #PPcentered I wanted to share one of my favorite moments. Living in California you’re never too far from beautiful places like this. Only a 3hr drive from Los Angeles and you find yourself among some crazy rock formations in the Eastern Sierras. I particularly love this location because after spending the night under the stars you’re greeted with one of the most spectacular sunrises as the sun kisses the mountain peaks.

☁️Today’s thoughts☁️ I’m sure some of you can relate...sometimes I get in this creative funk and question what my motivations are with photography/instagram and for me it always goes back to why I create. Im reminded that I don’t create for the likes or the follows but to convey emotion from a moment in time. Creating has been something that I’ve always loved doing since way back in the day before insta, when I was in my driveway with the homies making videos of us playin ball or always being the one with the camera documenting times with friends and family. I feel most alive with a camera in my hand and I’m super grateful that I have this platform to share the moments I capture with all of you. Thank you for always supporting and showing love. It doesn’t go unnoticed. 🙏🏽 #menasthoughts
📸: @allyse.c

Soaring into 2018 like...only my second time on a helicopter, what an amazing experience flying over my city!

Looking back at this last year and I feel so blessed. Many of you may not know but I left my job earlier this year to travel. It has been one of the best decisions I’ve ever made. It wasn’t easy leaving the security of a stable job but life will only change when you become more committed to your dreams then to your comfort zone. I hope this video can convey even a fraction of what this experience has meant to me. Here’s to more adventures in 2018 🙏🏽 Enjoy!

Traveling in Myanmar for the last month has been the most enriching experience of my life. From meeting fellow travellers to sitting down and having lunch and tea with monks in a monastery to the 16 and 20 hour bus rides, I've taken it all in and I feel extremely blessed for the opportunity to come here. Myanmar is a mysterious land with so much that I have yet to discover. One thing I do know is the absolute beauty of its people, inside and out. It's time to end this chapter in my travels and begin the next but Myanmar I promise, I will be back!--------------------------------------------------Next stop ✈️ Hong Kong!
